  "prompt": "What is smart strategy to prepare for CMAT 2017?",
  "response": "Preparing for the CMAT (Common Management Admission Test) 2017 requires a strategic approach to ensure success. Here are a few smart strategies:\n\n1. **Understand the Exam Pattern and Syllabus**:\n   - Familiarize yourself with the four sections: Logical Reasoning, Language Comprehension, Quantitative Techniques & Data Interpretation, and General Awareness.\n   - Each section has 25 questions, totaling 100 questions. The test duration is 180 minutes.\n   - Knowing the weightage of each section will help in prioritizing your study plan.\n\n2. **Create a Study Schedule**:\n   - Allocate specific time slots for each section.\n   - Ensure you balance your study schedule to cover all sections comprehensively.\n   - Allow time for revision and practice tests.\n\n3. **Conceptual Clarity**:\n   - Focus on understanding the concepts rather than rote learning.\n   - For Quantitative Techniques, ensure you cover basic mathematical concepts like arithmetic, geometry, and algebra.\n   - Strengthen your vocabulary and grammar for the Language Comprehension section.\n\n4. **Practice Regularly**:\n   - Solve previous years' question papers to understand the type of questions.\n   - Take mock tests to simulate the exam condition and improve time management.\n   - Analyze your performance in these tests and work on the weak areas.\n\n5. **Improve Speed and Accuracy**:\n   - Logical Reasoning requires quick thinking; practice puzzles and reasoning questions daily.\n   - For Quantitative Techniques, practice shortcut methods to solve problems faster.\n   - Enhance accuracy to minimize negative marking.\n\n6. **Stay Updated on Current Affairs**:\n   - Read newspapers daily and follow current events for General Awareness.\n   - Focus on significant events from the past year.\n\n7. **Resources**:\n   - Use reliable study materials and reference books.\n   - Online resources, coaching centers, and study groups can be helpful.\n\n8. **Healthy Routine**:\n   - Ensure regular breaks during your study sessions.\n   - Maintain a healthy lifestyle, including proper diet and sleep to keep your mind fresh.\n\n9. **Revision**:\n   - Regularly revise concepts and practice questions.\n   - Focus on areas where you make frequent mistakes.\n\nFollowing these strategies diligently will help you prepare effectively for CMAT 2017 and improve your chances of securing a good score. Good luck!",
